# ============================================================
# visdrone-patch-attacks
# Keeps: *.py  *.log  *.md  *.yaml  results.json  *.boxes.json  universal_patch.png
# Drops: datasets, rendered figures, archives, model/patch weights
# ============================================================

# datasets: exclude the 54G of imagery, but KEEP the label .txt files.
# Labels are the custom 5-class remap (0=car 1=van 2=truck 3=bus 4=motor) and are
# required by make_figures_*.py / load_car_boxes() to reconstruct any figure.
# Cannot use a bare "datasets/" here: git cannot re-include inside an excluded dir.
/datasets/*
!/datasets/VisDrone/
/datasets/VisDrone/*
!/datasets/VisDrone/labels/

# rendered figure sets (regenerable from boxes.json + patch)
annotated/

# archives
*.zip

# raster figures (universal_patch.png is intentionally NOT excluded)
*.jpg
*.jpeg

# torch weights: exclude by default (retinanet/effdet checkpoints are large)...
*.pt
# ...but KEEP the two irreplaceable kinds -- they cannot be regenerated off-machine.
# NOTE: no trailing comments on these lines -- gitignore treats them as part of the pattern.
# 127 trained patches, 228M total, largest 43M:
!universal_patch.pt
# fine-tuned detector, 48.9M, under GitHub's 100M cap:
!yolo11l_visdrone_pretrained.pt
# other trained checkpoints, all under the 100M cap:
!best.pt
!efficientdet_d3.pt
!yolo11l_combined_scratch.pt
!yolov5s_visdrone_10class.pt
# NOTE: retinanet_{custom,standard,v2_custom}.pt stay excluded -- 121/123/121 MB,
# over GitHub's 100 MB hard limit; they would break the push.

# local archives -- must never enter the repo
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.tar

# derived copies made in-session; their boxes.json duplicate patch_examples_*
table_runs/

# local noise
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store

# Claude session transcript (kept outside the repo / on Drive)
conversation_transcript.jsonl
conversation_memory.md
